            <thetext>Calling the getChildren method of a qx.ui.form.DateField instance causes an Exception: TypeError: container[functionName] is not a function. This happens because qx.ui.core.MRemoteChildrenHandling forwards the call to the childrenContainer, which evaluates to the &quot;list&quot; child control. This works for select boxes but not for the DateField where the &quot;list&quot; child control is actually the DateChooser widget which has no getChildren method.

A simple solution would be to add a getChildren method to DateChooser that always returns an empty array.</thetext>
